caption: The food here is pretty epic and the service is one of a kind. They have an awesome menu selection too and I do recommend you try these guys out.
Good atmosphere
Best drinks I've ever had in DC. Their truffle fries were also amazing, and their chairs are super comfortable to boot. Can't wait to go back!
Great food great people great place...

Sitting inside the restaurant while posting this. We randomly entered since we were looking for a vegetarian friendly restaurant to eat. The vibe and the service made our day!!! I would rate this as one of the best and most friendly places in DC for sure. The food was so so good!! Also the review would be incomplete without a shoutout to Becca for being the most friendly and humble human being i have ever come across 💖
We made a reservation ahead of time for outdoor seating ( bc Covid) but when we got there they told us they didn’t have a table for us. We offered to wait and they refused to seat us at all.
Nice option for summer nights. The cheese and meat boards are awesome.
Great place and small plates for sharing, and very good service.
Popped in walking by and enjoyed every min. Service was incredible. Dining was outstanding. Will definitely suggest having a meal here. We will be returning !!

Always a pleasant time whenever going. The staff are super friendly and attentive. Food and drinks are great too. They've earned a new regular. This place is a go-to for a relaxed time to blow off steam and chill. Strongly recommend. Shout out to Becca for the great service!
Nero is great inside as it is it's patio...great service (Becka is the best) and the most delicious pizza selection. If you want to relax and have a great time with friends, this is the place.

The staff is great! Everyone is very friendly and adequately masked. Though it's a limited menu during covid, the available food and drinks are very well made. I look forward to trying the wine vending selection and the Indian dish offerings when things fully reopen!

Couldn't love Nero more! Delicious cocktails, outstanding food (simple, tasty, but still elegant!) and phenomenal customer service by management and staff. The ambiance is warm, comfortable and modern: great for a special occasion or just for when you're looking for a swanky hang. Cannot WAIT to go back!
Very lovely place nice food , romantic vibes but only order pizza if you are hungry. , All other plates are very small. Tasty but small.
What a wonderful little bar! Had a great experience. Definitely worth hitting up before the clubs get rolling.

It is a great hideaway. The bar looks like an underground speakeasy. There is good specials for the happy hour. The decoration and atmosphere are great. There are a lot of wines on tap, and tons of other drinks.
This is not the Dupont bar we're used to. Great ambiance, great cocktails, and some of the best wine selection in the city. Look for Catherine and Kamila, they made some excellent cocktails.
Delicious craft cocktails and the atmosphere is so relaxing

Stopped in for drinks at happy hour. Friendly bartenders. I enjoyed the atmosphere a great deal. Interesting decor and a great playlist. Limited selections on the happy hour menu, but what they did have was decent enough.
If you can handle small, tight spaces, but love good atmosphere, friendly service, and tasty food & beverage, give Nero a visit.
Upscale, exclusive-feeling neighborhood bar in DC that serves a variety of delicious Pinot Noir wine varieties. Look forward to visiting again sometime soon!

Staff was incredibly sweet while also bring extremely efficient on a busy night with a private event. Cocktails were great. Fried brussel sprouts were wonderful. (I happily ate the entire plate by myself).  10/10 would recommend.

We arrived just before happy hour ended. Ordered a round of drinks and apps off the happy hour menu, then stayed for several hours. Great ambience, great music, and very chill lounge in the back. However, when we received our check we were charged full price for our first round and apps, which were ordered during happy hour. Waitress was not helpful in fixing this and rather than argue we just paid. Bummer because it was otherwise a really great spot.

Small place and I don't like crowded places like that. The back of Nero had space to dance and was pretty decent. The staff though are awesome people. No attitudes and they always had a smile on their faces and even made quick small talk. Very nice environment though. Its not a place I would go to due to the size, however if there is an event happening there that I want to attend, I won't hesitate to attend. Definitely a more friendly place then Dirty Martini staff was.

Food is excellent. Love the fries and pizza. The first time I had an old fashioned here it was incredible--it was called blood orange smoked old fashioned or something and it was amazing. The second time wasn't that great but more typical of old fashioned cocktails in most places, not worth $15.
Great place for drinks
Great atmosphere and decore. I was suggested Livia's lust martini and it didn't disipoint!
They lit my drink on fire

The DOPEST spot in Dupont! Katherine is an absolute gem, the food the WINE, absolutely spot on. I had the Fried Mozzarella and the Truffle Fries, all absolutely delicious. I am now a regular. And being a history buff, this place is named after one of the most infamous Roman Emporers that ever reigned, right next to Caligula!!! This place is dope!!!
Michelin quality servers
Service was amazing. Fries was the best.
Good play
Great food, mostly good selection, although they had run out of two of my party's first choices. Service was good but a little on the slow side. Will definitely return.
Cool cozy club joint with a DJ. Passed by on a Saturday. Quick bar service also.

Went for happy hour and our party was served by Red, who was attentive and just plain awesome. The pizza here is legit, with a crust that still makes my mouth water. The lamb samosas and truffle fries were also a hit. The cocktails were tasty and priced right. We'll be back for more of that 24-hour aged crust!
Good wine and beer variety. Super friendly helpful and knowledgeable staff.
The bartender Red provided excellent customer service. The drinks were great and a good location in DuPont Circle.
Loveeed it!!!!!!! Best customer service and bartender we great!!!!! Red was awesome!!!!

Lot’s of energy!!! Fantastic cocktails, 20+ variety of red and white wines in wine vending machine. Great for wine tasting!!! good selection of appetizers and interesting dinner menu a blend of Italian American flavors... loved their mushroom truffle pizza! Old fashioned is pretty good!

First time visit NERO and it was really good for me it was not like a club. However you can dance like next to the bar and have a drink and in the back is seating area with tables and chairs very chill and the vibes are amazing. I will be coming back in the future. Stay cool Nero
Hip little DC surprise

NERO serves all your Italian desires in DuPont Circle. Between a wonderfully friendly staff, an unbeatable bohemian atmosphere, and food that'll knock your tongue right out of your head, there are few comparable choices for lunchtime goodness. The panino is especially recommended for you meat lovers out there, but any pizza is also an excellent choice.
Bartender took over 45 min to get my order and then rang my tab on the wrong card. Had to order from the other bartender

Great new trendy Dupont Circle restaurant. Small menu but absolutely on point. It’s dark and cozy, in my opinion the perfect spot for a date. Great wine selection and decent beer selection as well. The Brussels sprouts, truffle fries, and mushroom pizza were fantastic. My new number one date spot in Dupont.
Great food, great drinks, best bar and lounge in DuPont circle!

(Translated by Google) Very nice place, ideal for a drink with friends in a relaxing environment. Waitresses at the top! I highly recommend.  (Original) Endroit très sympathique, idéal pour boire un verre entre amis dans un cadre relaxant. Serveuses au top ! Je recommande fortement.

The pizza was amazing! Cherries on pizza, who knew, but it absolutely works! Also, great wine at affordable prices. It's like an arcade with the claw game, without the claw, and you always win the wine. I loved it.
Nice bar. I enjoyed my visit

Great wine selection (buy a wine card and try whatever you like!) And great pizza/Italian bites. Relaxed, laid-back vibe where you can hear people talk, though it does get clubby later at night on weekends. Good happy hour deals!
Nice place, good food but noisy and tiny table to try to eat on.
Really fun dinner date spot.  Lively, great food (get the Tandoori pops), and solid wine selection.
Great pub
Such a cute and cozy environment

Got here Saturday night, still somewhat early, talking about 11ish, and decided to come in because everywhere else had a long line. I was very pleased especially with the bartender. I dont remember her name but she was nice and very responsive. Will go back again.
Delicious drinks and cozy atmosphere.

(Translated by Google) Super nice place, music top and many wines à la carte. Super friendly servers!  (Original) Endroit super sympa, music top et nombreux vins à la carte. Serveurs super accueillants !
Great bar! Lost my phone and the manager even let me borrow his phone to call one of my friends
Great atmosphere food and cocktails...perfect for a date and awesome place to hang out with Friends!!!
all the staff is really great and it is really clean and pretty in here, not as crowded as next door  Anita and Lindsey are the best!!!!
best indian bar food I have had in dc
awesome place to hang out with friends, great food and really fast too

Excellent venue for drinks, dinner, or a quick snack. Jonas, Cat, and the rest of the staff are quick and friendly. Upscale feel but the food and drinks are both great value. Will definitely be back soon for more!
I love Nero. It’s a nice place where you can relax and try a variety of craft  coctails. Their chicken samosas are great. Staff is nice and friendly.
Great atmosphere! The tandoori pops we delicious!!!

Came across this place on a Sunday afternoon and was beyond surprised. This is a fantastic date spot with a great environment. The staff is  extremely responsive and friendly. I highly recommend the Tandoori pops. I’ll definitely be coming back soon.
MY NEW FAVORITE SPOT! I was walking past and noticed it for the first time. Jonas was very friendly and knowledgeable about his spirits and took great care of our group. Try the samosas!

DON'T GO THERE. JONAS THE BARTENDER WILL CHARGE YOU $73.00 FOR THREE SHOTS OF TULLAMORE DEW THAT COSTS ONLY $12 EVERYWHERE ELSE. DID NOT WANT TO ARGUE WITH HIM BUT WILL DEF GET MY MONEY BACK. ZERO(0) FOR THIS ESTABLISHMENT. CALLED VIC TO SETTLE ISSUE BUT NOTHING WAS DONE
Sat at bar for almost 15 mins and not a single person walked up to us. It wasn't even crowded. We left after 16 minutes.
Dont be intimidated by the lights. Great place if there's space. Music is a little loud but easy to drink through.
Great atmosphere and cocktails...perfect for a date night and then great dj / dancing late night!
Great place to hang out with nice ambiance, drinks, food and staff. Do check out their happy hours!
Nice atmosphere and great music. Great place for a date or ladies night.
